      <elementaryExchange id="d58fad04-52eb-557e-bb40-86e0d65e4e1b" unitId="eb955b7c-7bed-401f-9c76-5db716ca3640" amount="0.000129417297521154" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="(0.024+0.035)/2*10^4/(519000*21.96/5)" elementaryExchangeId="c991a302-884f-4882-a094-e1b8f1d4c6b0">
        <name xml:lang="en">Occupation, bare area (non-use)</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m2*year</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Estimated for infrastructure. Land occupation calculated as the land occupied by the production facility (average 0.024-0.035 ha) divided by the amount of material produced per year at the facility, considering that the adobe brick production in Azuay province is 519000 bricks/year, where there are 5 production areas (see PV comment in EC dataset), and each brick weights on average 21.96 kg.

The ecoinvent data quality guidelines (Section 6.7 Land occupation and transformation, Table 6.1) defins this exchange as follows: "Bare area (non-use): Areas permanently without vegetation (e.g., deserts, high alpine area...)". Such definition is the best fit to the case described in this dataset. Indeed, the factories visited are lcoated on open land areas, usually away from cities, with bare soil on which the producers use the hand-powered machines. There is no complex infrastructure around, in the best case only a simple structure for coverage is made available. The exchanges "Industrial area" and "Urban/industrial fallow (non-use)" are not used, as they would overestimate the impacts, since in the Ecuadorian workshops there are no actual buildings, no asphalted roads, no houses around. </comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.000129417297521154" mu="-8.952468510015438" variance="0.04" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.04320000000000001"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="1" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="1"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <property propertyId="f2283db2-62e4-467f-b9ac-c4f45be563b4" amount="0.0" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
